.TH VKSTG "1"

.SH NAME
.B vkstg.pl 
- Validator for KJEntytek's Simple Transfur Generator

.SH SYNOPSIS
\&./vkstg.pl

.SH DESCRIPTION
VKSTG is a validator and macro processor for
.B kstfg(1).
It's primary job is to validate the provided variant klofs, and expand all the presets used, so other generators don't have to worry about them.

By default, VKSTG expects a klof input at STDIN, and prints a processed file to STDOUT.

.SH HOW VKSTG WORKS

VKSTG begins by scanning STDIN for input. 
It waits for EOF (which can be manually generated by pressing C-d if running interactively),
and once EOF is detected, VKSTG begins validation.

At first, VKSTG iterates over all lines from STDIN, and removes comments and blank lines, see
.B klof(5)
for reference.
Next, VKSTG checks if lines inside of a file match the rules specified below, and prints the processed input file to STDOUT but without blank lines or comments.
One special case is the
.B PRESETS=[]
array, which is resolved by recursively calling VKSTG by shelling out, and taking it's STDOUT and appending it to the beginning of a processed file.
.br
.B Note:
VKSTG will crash if the preset file is invalid or doesn't exist.

.SH VALID KLOF KEYWORDS

Valid scalars:

.RS 4
.B EXTEND=
- Checks for valid java class names
.br
.B TRANSFUR_SOUND=
- resource location of the sound. Typically handled with method calls.
.br
.B TRANSFUR_MODE=
- Valid values: ABSORPTION, REPLICATION, NONE
.B MINING=
- Valid values: WEAK, NORMAL, STRONG
.br
.B ENTITY_SHAPE=
- Valid values: ANTHRO, FERAL, TAUR, NAGA, MER
.br
.B USE_ITEM_MODE=
- Valid values: NORMAL, MOUTH, NONE
.br
.B FLY
- Valid values: NONE, CT, ELYTRA, BOTH
.br
.B JUMPS=
- Valid values: non-negative integers (0, 1, 2...);
.br
.B VISION=
- Valid values: NORMAL, NIGHT_VISION, BLIND, REDUCED, VAVE_VISION
.br
.B CLIMB=
- Valid values: boolean
.br
.B Z_OFFSET=
- Valid values: floating point numbers.
.br
.B TICKS_TO_FREEZE=
- Valid values - non-negative integers.
.br
.B BREATH=
- Valid values: NORMAL, WATER, ANY, NONE
.br
.B POWDER_SNOW_WALKABLE=
- Valid values: boolean
.br
.B TRANSFUR_COLOR=
- Valid values: hexadecimals in C notation (example: 0x123456, 0xfedcba, 0x1F3c5A)
.br
.B ABILITY_COLOR_1ST=
.B ABILITY_COLOR_2ND=
- Valid values: hexadecimals on C notation
.br
.B LATEX_TYPE=
- Valid values: WHITE_LATEX, DARK_LATEX, NONE
.br
.B GENDER=
- Valid values: MALE, FEMALE. Warning: You probably shouldn't implement this manually, rely on
.B geng.pl(1)
instead.
.br
.B SPAWN_PLACEMENT=
- Valid values: ON_GROUND, IN_WATER, NO_RESTRICTIONS, IN_LAVA, null.
.br
.B SPAWN_HEIGHTMAP=
- Valid values: WORLD_SURFACE, WORLD_SURFACE_WG, OCEAN_FLOOR, OCEAN_FLOOR_WG, MOTION_BLOCKING, MOTION_BLOCKING_NO_LEAVES, null.
.br
.B BUILDER=
- Valid values: entity builder. This option is deprecated, but currently there are no alternatives.
.br
.B MIN_SPAWN=
- Valid values: non-negative integers.
.br
.B MAX_SPAWN=
- Valid values: non-negative integers.
.br
.B SPAWN_WEIGHT=
- Valid values: non-negative integers.
.br
.B RENDERER_TYPE=
- Valid values: None, unused for now.
.br
.B MULTIHANDED_RENDERER=
- valid values: boolean
.br
.B ARMOR_MODEL=
- Valid values: Armor model java classpath.
.br
.B EYES_PRESENT=
- Valid values: boolean
.br
.B IRIS_1ST_COLOR=
- Valid values: hexadecimals using C notation, optionally ending with a "dl" string.
Example: 0x123456dl, 0x654321
.br
.B IRIS_2ND_COLOR=
- Valid values: hexadecimals using C notation, optionally ending with a "dl" string.
.br
.B SCLERA_COLOR=
- Valid values: hexadecimals using C notation, optionally ending with a "dl" string.
.br
.B GAS_MASK_LAYER=
- Valid values: java class path to a proper model layer
.br
.B IS_MASKED=
- Valid values: boolean
.br
.B EMISSIVE_LAYER=
- Valid values: boolean
.br
.B TRANSLUCENT_LAYER
- Valid values: boolean
.br
.B MODEL_SCALE=
- Valid values: floating point numbers
.br
.B SHADOW_SIZE=
- Valid values: floating point numbers
.br
.B ANIM_PRESET=
- Valid values: unused.
.br
.B RIDING_OFFSET=
- Valid values: floating point numbers
.br
.B GENDERED=
- Valid values: boolean.

.RE

Valid arrays:

.RS 4
.B ABILITIES=[]
.br
.B ATTRIBUTES=[]
.br
.B SCARES=[]
.br
.B DIMENSIONS=[]
.RE

Special keywords:

.RS 4
.B TEMPLATE=VALUE
- Special, checks for a file data/java/tf-templates/VALUE.java.template
.br
.B RENDERER_TEMPLATE=VALUE
- Special, checks for a file data/java/renderers/VALUE.java.template
.br
.B ACCESSORIES=VALUE
- Special, checks for a file data/data/additional_tranfurs/accessories/VALUE

.RE
Array mode special keywords:

.RS 4
.B PRESETS=[
.br
.B ARRAY_VALUES
.br
.B ]
.br
Special, checks for file inside data/klofs/presets/ARRAY_VALUE.klof, and expands them at the beginning of a file.

.B TAGS=[
.br
.B NAMESPACE:TAG_IDS
.br
.B ]
.br
Special, checks for tag ids, according to regex
.B /((^[a-z][a-z0-9_]*):([a-z][a-z0-9_\/]*))\h*(false|)?\h*$/
and checks if a file exists inside data/NAMESPACE/tags/entity_types/TAG_ID.mctag

.RE

.SH BUGS
VKSTG might contain deprecated and unused keywords that will past tests.
These are mostly harmless, as applications using klof files should ignore their invalid entries and rely on VKSTG to validate their configs.
